  "summary": "client-cookies-agent postinstall beacons host identifiers to oast.fun",
  "details": "client-cookies-agent 99.9.7 ships only index.js + package.json with empty description/author/keywords and version 99.9.7 (dependency-confusion style high version). package.json declares scripts.postinstall: \"node index.js\", so on `npm install` the script runs automatically and collects os.hostname(), process.cwd(), os.userInfo().username, and the machine's non-internal IPv4 address, then POSTs them as JSON to https://lpzlajzjfkpfeefuzxbv6n5nob7bpuh6e.oast.fun/receive-data. oast.fun is an out-of-band interaction (OAST) callback service used to receive exfiltrated data from within a victim network. The package has no other functionality — the beacon is its sole purpose.",
